        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:24PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>At 523 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Waverly to 6 miles southeast of Hopkinton
to near Colton. Movement was southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Adirondack Regional Airport, Saranac Lake, Tupper Lake Village, Lake
Placid, Franklin, Tupper Lake, Piercefield, Wilmington, North Elba,
Waverly, Harrietstown, Colton, Santa Clara, Brighton, St Armand,
Keene, Duane, Black Brook, Hopkinton, and Newcomb.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
